1. *Ramena* me bole od nošenja teških torbi. (*Ramena* - Nominative case, "shoulders" - My shoulders hurt from carrying heavy bags.)
2. Drago mi je što si se *rama* dotakao svojih neostvarenih ciljeva. (*Rama* - Genitive case, "shoulder" - I'm glad you've touched upon your unrealized goals.)
3. Uvek *ramenima* pokrivaj usta kada kašlješ ili kišeš. (*Ramena* - Instrumental case, "with your shoulders" - Always cover your mouth when you cough or sneeze with your shoulders.)
4. *Ramena* su mu se opustila nakon napornog dana na poslu. (*Ramena* - Nominative case, "shoulders" - His shoulders relaxed after a hard day at work.)
5. Sestra mi je kupila prelepu haljinu koja mi lepo ističe *ramena*. (*Ramena* - Accusative case, "shoulders" - My sister bought me a beautiful dress that highlights my shoulders nicely.)
6. Izvukao me je iz gomile ljudi tako što mi je uhvatio *ramena*. (*Ramena* - Accusative case, "shoulders" - He pulled me out of the crowd by grabbing my shoulders.)
7. Ona voli da nosi torbe preko *ramena*. (*Ramena* - Genitive case, "shoulder" - She likes to carry bags over her shoulder.)
8. *Ramenu* je potrebna fizička terapija nakon povrede. (*Ramenu* - Dative case, "shoulder" - The shoulder needs physical therapy after an injury.)
9. Kada sam se naslonila na njegovo *rameno* krilo, osetila sam se sigurno. (*Rameno* - Adjective, "shoulder" - When I leaned on his shoulder, I felt safe.)
10. Moramo podići nivo svesti o važnosti zaštite *ramena* tokom sportskih aktivnosti. (*Ramena* - Genitive case, "shoulder" - We need to raise awareness about the importance of protecting shoulders during sports activities.)